column31: Thyroid function affects the entire body, so if you have hypothyroidism, which is an underactive thyroid, you will see a host of symptoms. On the flip side, an overactive thyroid, an equally problematic condition, is called hyperthyroid. Among women, especially those in child-bearing years and menopause, hypothyroid is very common. However, most physicians will dose medications off of TSH levels — levels that do not accurately depict what is going on in the thyroid. And to make matters worse, they prescribe T4 only, which can actually make the problem worse. Do you have hypothyroidism?

When I was pregnant with my first, I knew nothing, I mean NOTHING, about vaccines. Yet, I wasn’t born yesterday. I knew pesticides were poisonous, and aluminum in deodorant was toxic. I could easily recognize that the people who took the most prescription medications (as a bandaid) were the least healthy. I knew the Standard American Diet (SAD) was processed and unhealthy, and that artificial flavor and food coloring was complete garbage. I knew most of these corporations didn’t genuinely care about our health (I mean why put dangerous ingredients in children’s products in the first place, derived from coal tar or aluminum, parabens cause cancer, high fructose corn syrup causes diabetes & obesity). Why even do that?!? And then there’s vaccines. You know, the irony of it all is THEY use fear-based propaganda even though THEIR products are the scariest of all. They stick needles into perfectly healthy babies, and force parents to ignore their intuition around this. We know, deep down inside, that this is wrong. But we are afraid to speak up. We are afraid we don’t have all the information. We want to trust our doctors, scientists. I get it. But they don’t know everything. They are only humans. I can say now, I am shocked more people don’t ask questions. Some of the stuff I have come across over the years, like a SIDS infant was 7 times more likely to have received a DPT vaccine within 30 days of their death than >30 days. The information is out there. That delaying that first vaccine just 3 months reduces asthma risk by 2 thirds. See all my vaccine studies. column31: Why are antibiotics used as an ingredient in some vaccines? Neomycin is one of the antibiotics used. Is it to prevent contamination in the vial? Why are babies so young being exposed to antibiotics? “Vaccines work” you guys. They “work” by impairing your immune system so that it doesn’t respond properly to viral infection. "Antibiotics can have a negative impact on the microbiota, immunity and health". "Antibiotic administration can alter intestinal commensal bacterial populations and, as a consequence, modify immune defenses leading, in some cases, to detrimental effects on health". "Commensal microbial species that inhabit the intestinal tract contribute to the development, maintenance and function of the immune system". “Neomycin, an antibiotic that predominantly kills Gram-negative bacteria, is most effective at impairing anti-influenza responses.” “By using various antibiotic treatments, we found that neomycin-sensitive bacteria are associated with the induction of productive immune responses in the lung.” “Notably, we found that neomycin-sensitive bacteria contributed to immunocompetence in the lung.” “Thus, our data reveal a key role for commensal bacteria in controlling adaptive immunity against a respiratory virus infection.” In other words: We need a healthy microbiome for our immune systems to respond properly to viral infection (including proper immune response in the lungs, to respiratory pathogens), and neomycin kills the bacteria which are critical for proper immune system response to influenza/respiratory pathogen. And neomycin kills that bacteria. Merck, GSK, Sanofi: “Hey, let’s put it in vaccines!” Content shared via @AshleyEverly https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3427468/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3069176/

column31: We are outside this morning hiking and playing ball, watching the gorgeous sunrise, getting the sun's rays directly on our face! Did you know your eyes and your skin are your solar panels?! If you charge them correctly, they will power your entire body. When we talk about benefits of sunlight, we think vitamin D, but the details and role that the sun plays in the human body goes far further. Scientifically, sunshine has a lot of benefits for our bodies. Here are seven great reasons to get outside and soak in the sun. 1. Improves your sleep Your body creates a hormone called melatonin that is critical to helping you sleep. Because your body starts producing it when it’s dark, you usually start to feel sleepy two hours after the sun sets, which is one of the reasons our bodies naturally stay up later in the summer. Research indicates that an hour of natural light in the morning will help you sleep better. Sunshine regulates your circadian rhythm by telling your body when to increase and decrease your melatonin levels. So, the more daylight exposure you can get, the better your body will produce melatonin when it’s time to go to sleep. 2. Reduces stress Melatonin also lowers stress reactivity and being outside will help your body naturally regulate melatonin, which can help reduce your stress level. Additionally, because you're often doing something active when you’re outside (walking, playing, etc.), that extra exercise also helps to lower stress. 3. Maintains strong bones One of the best (and easiest) ways to get vitamin D is by being outside. Our bodies produce vitamin D when exposed to sunlight—about 15 minutes in the sun a day is adequate if you’re fair skinned. And since Vitamin D helps your body maintain calcium and prevents brittle, thin, or misshapen bones, soaking in sun may be just what the doctor ordered. 4. Helps keep the weight off (hello!) Getting outside for 30 minutes sometime between 8 a.m. and noon has been linked to weight loss. There are other factors linked to this, of course, but it seems there's a connection between sunlight in the early morning and weight loss. 5. Strengthens your immune system (critical every day, but especially right now) Vitamin D is also critical for your immune system, and with consistent exposure to sunlight, you can help strengthen it. A healthy immune system can help reduce the risk of illness, infections, some cancers, and mortality after surgery. 6. Fights off depression and other mood imbalances It’s not just in your head; there’s a scientific reason being in the sunshine improves your mood. Sunshine boosts your body’s level of serotonin, which is a chemical that improves your mood and helps you stay calm and focused. Increased exposure to natural light may help ease the symptoms of seasonal affective disorder--a change in mood that typically occurs in the fall and winter months when there are fewer hours of daylight. UVA light also triggers the production of serotonin and dopamine and releases endorphins along with a small opiate effect. The end result - you feel good. 7. Can give you a longer life A study that followed 30,000 Swedish women revealed that those who spent more time in the sun lived six months to two years longer than those with less sun exposure. More research needs to be done in this area, but it’s something scientists are continuing to study. Do you love watching the sun rise too?

column31: Most people are used to seeing sort of...odd...language on natural products. "May promote..." "Supports the function of..." Lots of people are left scratching their heads. What does all that *mean?* And if natural products really work, why don't companies just come out and say that?! Because they can't. The FDA doesn't regulate natural products or companies, but they do regulate what goes on the labels. If a product is not FDA-approved (which would make it a 'drug'), then companies cannot say that their product can treat, prevent, or cure anything. They can only make 'structure/function' claims. This is true even if companies have done clinical research to prove what their products can do, or if they have any other studies on the ingredients. It would still be an illegal drug claim. When you look at natural products, you have to read between the lines and do your own research on the ingredients. Many have a lot of potential benefits. There are good intentions behind these laws -- to prevent unscrupulous companies from making ridiculous or 'miracle' type claims -- but they also tie the hands of many companies, preventing them from telling the full truth. Another thing to watch out for is the disclaimers. Two you'll often see are "This product has not been evaluated by the FDA, and is not intended to diagnose, treat, or cure anything" and "Talk to a doctor before use if you are pregnant or breastfeeding." These are standard disclaimers, and often required by law. They don't mean the product is unsafe. If you're ever unsure, the best plan is to talk to a qualified herbalist, naturopath, or other natural-minded health practitioner to ask what would be both safe, and healthy for you to use. They can guide you -- and tell you the truth.

column31: Another example of vaccine "efficacy". England, 1852: Compulsory vaccination against smallpox introduced. 1857-1859: Smallpox epidemic kills 14,244 people. 1863-1865: Another epidemic kills 20,059 people. 1867: Even stricter vaccination law passed, including prosecution for those who refuse. 1871: Chief Medical Officer of England announces vaccination rate of 97.5% has been achieved. 1872: Worst ever smallpox epidemic, 44,840 people die. column31: "Freedom of speech" is not for benign statements. No one was ever challenging those. (Such as "I like playing with my kids" or "I'm going to work today.") It's exclusively for speech that is controversial or even hated. That is the speech that needs defending. That is the speech some would try to entirely shut down. These days, that debate is being reframed. People are considering certain types of speech (even general ideas not aimed at specific people, like medical freedom) to be "hate speech," and they consider it so damaging that it must be stopped and punished. What those people are advocating for is abject tyranny. If we are not free to share (and also, challenge) ideas, we are not free at all. We are under someone's thumb. Don't like what someone is saying? Use your own voice to speak up. You don't just get to decide you are right and silence them. Look into "The Center for Countering Digital Hate," which includes in their mission de-platforming individuals and punishing platforms with new laws for failing to act, when people engage in "denial of scientific consensus." Denial of scientific consensus -- discussion of science, asking questions. THEY THINK THIS SHOULD BE ILLEGAL. We live in a very dangerous world right now.

column31: November is Epilepsy Awareness Month. Epilepsy is a common neurological condition. About 1 in 200 children are diagnosed with it. This is Ali's story. https://avn.org.au/2018/10/gone-too-soon-alina-ali-poppy-murtagh-killed-by-vaccination/ She died from severe complications following the Measles Mumps Rubella Varicella (MMRV Priorix-Tetra) and Diphtheria Tetanus Pertussis (DTaP Infanrix) vaccinations she received on 4th November 2017, at 18 months of age. Ali’s parents and childcare service noticed changes in her almost immediately, including marked somnolence (sleepiness), and loss of interest in eating and social interaction, all of which are classic symptoms of encephalopathy, a well-documented side-effect of all vaccines. Within six days post-vaccination she was admitted to hospital with seizures. Although she was discharged following treatment soon after, it wasn’t long before Ali developed severe refractory Epilepsy, from which she did not recover. Such severity of her seizures, by January her brain had atrophied by approximately 50 percent, compared with her first MRI in November 2017. Ali finally lost her battle four months after her vaccinations, in March 2018. Convulsions, seizures, encephalitis, and encephalopathy are all listed in vaccine inserts as adverse reactions following vaccination. " Vaccine-induced encephalitis" was the reason for the global shift from whole-cell pertussis vaccine to acellular in the 90s. Measles Mumps Rubella - MMR https://childrenshealthdefense.org/research_tags/measles-mumps-rubella-mmr/ Seizures from the measles, mumps, and rubella (MMR) vaccine occur in about 1 in 640 children. https://physiciansforinformedconsent.org/mmr-seizures/ Education committee 2017. column31: All everyone wants to talk about these days is "We're in a pandemic! Get over it and just wear your mask!" They feel like we can deal with 'everything else' later, when it's over. But what will be left of our society by then? People's mental health is being severely affected, children in particular. column31: Friends, I'd love for you to weigh in on URGES and DECISIONS! 👉 Do you tend to make decisions primarily via Prefrontal cortex/modern brain (front) aka adult brain OR Primal/primitive/reptilian brain (basal ganglia)(hind) aka toddler brain? Let's talk primal brain and prefrontal cortex and how they relate to our food choice success and drive, the importance of planning what you’re going to eat ahead of time and how to manage urges! I work with a lot of clients with insulin resistance, weight concerns, mood ups and downs and blood sugar effects. These issues effect the signals in our bodies in terms of hunger and fullness and many times they are not accurate in the sense that we have completely thrown our bodies off by the food [and chemicals] that we have put into them; mainly sugar, flour and refined and processed foods that our hormones and neurotransmitters don’t really know what to do with them. When we’re eating those types of foods and then we start to try and tune into our body, our hunger signals, our hormones and cell receptor sites are so off that we feel like we’re hungry all of the time. So even though we may be eating only when we’re hungry, we’re eating too much because our body is actually craving food that it doesn’t actually need for fuel. We make decisions primarily via two (2) types of brain regions. 1.) Prefrontal cortex/modern brain (front). Problem solving, memory, language, judgment, impulse control, reasoning, long term goals, thoughtfulness, personal growth decisions and creating the best version of you. ❌Adult brain. 2.) Primal/primitive/reptilian brain (basal ganglia)(hind). What is satisfying and gratifying NOW and in the moment, survival, drive and instinct. ❌Toddler brain. Letting the primal brain make decisions (unless it's an emergency) is a tragedy. It leads to weight gain and overindulgence and buffering in a way that causes us tons of results that we don’t want. What you need to do is look at the brain decision-making process and utilize the most powerful part of your human brain, which is your prefrontal cortex. That is the part of your brain that separates you from animalistic behavior, primal behavior. That is the part of the brain where you can look ahead and you can plan and you can make decisions as an emotional adult. I like to compare it to the difference between a toddler and an adult. You can look into the future, delay gratification, give up what you want now for what you want most. You can take care of yourself even though you may not feel the immediate gratification from it. Plan out your meals ahead of time and stick to that plan.🍽 If we’re not planning ahead in terms of what we’re going to put in our body, that means relying on our primal brain to make those decisions in the moment and it’s completely unfair to our future self because the primal brain will always choose immediate pleasure. That is its job. And if you don’t override it with your prefrontal, human, higher level brain, you will be always at the effect of instant gratification. Because there’s so much instant gratification available, you will over-consume, which will create undesirable effect in the way you feel and probably in the way you carry your weight. There are several steps to this, however, step one is going to really be about utilizing that prefrontal. The concept is, losing weight is a *series* of small decisions. Those decisions need to be made from your higher brain. Small decisions throughout the day, lead us to that big wonderful outcome. Stay the course with eating the health nutrient dense low carbohydrate food you have planned out ahead - and don't diverge, that's the primal (toddler brain) saying ...just do it! Many of us turn to food, and sometimes poor food choices 👉 because we don’t know how to process emotions and level UP that prefrontal cortex. Let me know your thoughts in the comments below!

column31: The get-out-of-jail free card isn’t a particular politician or an end to the lockdown or even a va((ine. 😁 The get-out-of-jail free card is V I S I O N 👀 A vision beyond what the eyes can see. A vision broad enough to picture a future (& present) that we want to inhabit. A vision for the world that starts with a small, attainable idea. 🌍 For example, if you want a garden in your backyard (where all you have currently is concrete & weeds 🌱) you have to visualize what you’d like to see first. Then, you make some plans, get some tools, roll up your sleeves, and one day get digging. The yard won’t transform overnight, but one day the garden you dreamed of becomes your new reality. It’s always best to begin in your own backyard. Vision helps you see beyond what’s in front of you. The Bible says “Without a vision, the people perish.” What’s your vision?

column31: Guys, what is learned helplessness? "A condition in which a person suffers from a sense of powerlessness, arising from a traumatic event or persistent failure to succeed. It is thought to be one of the underlying causes of depression." It's now come into the mindset of adults, children, and professionals. "The concept of learned helplessness was discovered accidentally by psychologists Martin Seligman and Steven F. Maier. They had initially observed helpless behavior in dogs that were classically conditioned to expect an electrical shock after hearing a tone." Some common symptoms of learned helplessness include: ⚠️ Low self-esteem ⚠️ Passivity ⚠️ Poor motivation ⚠️ Giving up ⚠️ Lack of effort ⚠️ Frustration ⚠️ Procrastination ⚠️ Not researching on your own ⚠️ Failure to ask for help ⚠️ Repeating what main stream media says ⚠️ Not learning to take charge of your own body, health and life ⚠️ Staying glued to "authority and experts" on how to proceed and live Problem ➜ Reaction ➜ Solution. column31: A beautiful body || In a toxic world In this day and age, we battle toxin loads that far surpass want any human before us has been exposed to. We accumulate these bio-degrading substances without trying; through the air we breathe, the liquids we drink, our daily self care products and in the food we eat. Toxins absolutely interfere with the bodies innate healing potential. Your glymphatic/lymphatic system’s, liver/gallbladder, kidneys, lungs, skin, blood and gastrointestinal tract work together to innately keep you healthy. These are your channels of elimination and are very important. This is how your body works for you, not against you. Did you know that increased toxicity creates decreased innate body intelligence? When you sleep, your brain drains by literally squeezing glimpse attic fluid around cerebral centers, clearing amyloid proteins, pathogens and suppressing inflammation. Why is it important to detox the liver? Your liver handles a lot of toxins. You need to detox these harmful compounds. And you need to keep them moving out of your liver and the rest of your body regularly to minimize their negative effects. If toxins pile up, it could lead to liver damage, as well as dis-ease in other parts of your body. For example, toxins may contribute to obesity, cancer, and dementia. And they could be a factor in complex chronic illnesses such as fibromyalgia. Keep in mind, there are two main ways your body gets rid of toxins. This is based on what type they are: +Water-soluble toxins can be sent directly to your kidneys and excreted in your urine. +Fat-soluble toxins are first metabolized in your liver to make them water-soluble. Then they can be excreted via your urine or bile. One of your body’s safeguards against toxins is that the blood collected from your gut goes to your liver first. The blood from your gut may be especially high in toxins if your gut is leaky. But what exactly are these toxins, and where do they come from? ++Man-made toxins Environmental health experts say we’re in the midst of a “colossal toxicological experiment.” Tens of thousands of chemicals have been used over the last few decades. But they haven’t been adequately tested for safety. Some sources of man-made toxins include (many of these we bring in ourselves): +Environmental pollutants: These include car exhaust, industrial pollutants, cigarette smoke, and pesticides like glyphosate. Besides chemicals, some pesticides and fertilizers contain toxic heavy metals. These can contaminate the air, water, and soil. +Your home: A few examples are bisphenol A (BPA) in plastics and perfluorinated chemicals (PFCs) in nonstick cookware. Other examples are flame retardants in sofas and formaldehyde in the glue of particleboard used in some furniture. +Personal care and cleaning products: The majority of these items contain artificial fragrances and other potentially toxic chemicals. These include phthalates, which can disrupt your hormones and block your uptake of iodide. +Healthcare products: This includes prescription, over-the-counter, and recreational drugs, which are chemical concoctions. It also includes dental materials. Some of these are still made with toxic heavy metals, including mercury. +Alcohol: No matter what form alcohol is in — beer, wine, or hard liquor — your liver has to detoxify it. The International Agency for Research on Cancer classifies alcohol as a carcinogen, read that again. It increases the risk of liver, colon, and breast cancers, among other types. +Food: Some food toxins are added, such as preservatives and artificial colors. +Pesticides taint many foods, too. ++Biological toxins Microbes create toxins, sometimes called biological toxins or biotoxins. You also produce toxins in the course of normal bodily functions or metabolism. These could harm your health if you’re unable to detoxify them or break them down. Here are some examples of biological toxins and other compounds your liver processes: +Ammonia: Bacteria and parasites create ammonia, adding to your toxin load. Your liver converts ammonia into urea so you can excrete it. +Hormones: Your hormones must be in proper balance. For example, excess estrogen is linked to problems like breast cancer and obesity. Your liver converts excess estrogen into a form you can excrete. Poor liver health can lead to excess estrogen. +Mycotoxins: Mold can produce harmful chemicals called mycotoxins. These contaminate water-damaged buildings, as well as some foods. Mold can also grow inside you and produce mycotoxins in your body. +Bacterial toxins: Harmful bacteria in water-damaged buildings and in your gut produce toxins. That includes endotoxins called lipopolysaccharides. These are from the outer membrane of bacteria. They can trigger inflammation in your body. Some possible symptoms of impaired liver function and detoxification include: Disturbed sleep Itchy skin (acne) Clammy hands Muscle pain or cramps Extreme tiredness Headaches Allergies of all (truncated)

column31: Dry skin can be such a battle during the cold, dry winter months. There is nothing fun about dry, itchy skin that flakes and cracks all the time. And while most of us enjoy the thought of maintaining soft, smooth skin all year round, the reality is that it is hard to do… especially with chemical laden lotions and body rubs. Natural skin care is super important, especially when it comes to dry, needy skin that soaks things up like a sponge. Apply harsh ingredients and you are asking for even more maintenance during this time of year. Commercial soaps might make you smell nice and clean, but they also strip your skin of important oils that protect and moisturize. Did you know that most commercial lotions you purchase at a department store can actually dry out and damage your skin more than moisturize it? It’s true. Take a look at the label… you might see alcohol, petroleum by-products, parabens, artificial fragrances and many other ingredients that half of us can’t pronounce. These ingredients destroy your body’s defense system, leaving is susceptible to all sorts of damage and the inability to restore its natural oils. Your skin needs foods high in fatty acids, fiber and raw nutrients. Whenever you can, incorporate fresh, wholesome foods into your diet. Focus on raw nuts and seeds, dark leafy greens and veggies, raw milk and organic butter, organic meats (including organ meats) and lots of water. Your body will be able to put these nutrients to good use and your skin will be noticeably happier. Always keep your skin well protected during the harsh, cold weather. This means bundle up before going outside to face cold wind, dry air and freezing snow. Your skin already works hard to protect your entire body, so help it out every once in a while! If you need product recommendations for dry skin, let us know! We have an awesome deal going on right now 🤗

column31: Aware friends, today, let's talk the Immune System and Molds. Many clients will scan for molds and/or have symptoms of mold toxicity and perhaps not even know the connection. Having these assessed and cleared by a skilled root cause practitioner will be important for short and long terms healing. Our immune systems protect us from dangerous pathogens, like bacteria, including Lyme’s Borrelia burgdorferi, parasites, viruses, and fungi (including mold). It shields us from the harmful substances we encounter, including environmental toxins, heavy metals, biotoxins, and more. White blood cells, called lymphocytes, carry out adaptive immune responses. There are two broad classes of these responses: cell-mediated immune responses and antibody responses. They are carried out by different types of lymphocytes, called T cells and B cells, respectively. In the cell-mediated immune response, activated T cells take direct action against foreign antigens. T cells might kill an infected or toxic host cell. Or, the T cell might produce a signal molecule that activates macrophages which engulf and destroy invaders, toxins, and cellular debris. Activated B cells secrete antibodies–proteins called immunoglobulins. The antibodies circulate in the system, where they bind specifically to the foreign antigens, inactivating the mold biotoxins. As a result, the biotoxins can no longer bind to receptors on host cells. Mycotoxin exposure comes from ingestion, dermal transmission, and inhalation. Mold toxins are extremely potent and often affect nearly every organ system in the body. Some of the symptoms associated with Chronic Inflammatory Response Syndrome (CIRS) include: +Brain fog, memory issues, cognitive and focus difficulties +Mood swings +Digestive problems +Fatigue; weakness +Frequent urination; excessive thirst; dehydration +Weight gain +Muscle and joint pain +Blurry vision; light sensitivity +Postnasal drip; sore throat +Numbness; tingling +Tinnitus +Static shocks +Dizziness +Metallic taste in the mouth +Low-grade fever +Shortness of breath +Headache Key elements of the immune system which I bioscan assess for clients include: 📈 +Spleen Your spleen helps your body fight infection. Just as it quality checks red blood cells, your spleen can identify unwelcome pathogens in your blood. In conjunction with the lymph nodes, it creates an organized force of defender cells called lymphocytes. Lymphocytes are specific white blood cells that produce antibodies. +Lymph Nodes These are nodes, vessels, and tissues located throughout the body, including in the neck, armpits, abdomen, and groin. The lymph nodes help break down harmful germs. Also, they filter toxins for removal from the body in lymph fluid. White blood cells contained in the lymph nodes help fight infection. +Bone Marrow Bone marrow is the spongy tissue located inside some of the bones in the body, such as the hip and thigh bones. Bone marrow makes 200 billion new red blood cells every day.3 It also produces white blood cells and platelets. If the bone marrow isn’t functioning well and produces abnormal white blood cells, those cells may be unable to fight infection. +White Blood Cells The bone marrow produces white blood cells, or leukocytes. These are crucial for a healthy immune system. They fight and protect against infections. They are stored in the spleen, the bone marrow, and the lymph nodes. White blood cells can circulate throughout the body. They collect in areas where there is an infection. +Mycotoxins can significantly impair the antibody production of the adaptive immune system. They can reduce the growth and spread of lymphocytes. 🍃 Since I am solution focused, here is a thorough article on how to handle mold deeply ➜ http://www.integrativenutritionaltherapies.com/conquering-candida-and-fungal-infections-permanently/ 🦠🦠 Here is a powerful supportive mold correcting kit I HIGHLY recommend ➜ https://bit.ly/2PahnOo

column31: "The only reason unvaccinated people don't get sick is because of herd immunity” NO. Vaccine induced herd immunity is a myth. Vaccine-Induced “herd immunity” is nothing more than a fear-based, guilt-tripping marketing tactic used the by the Pharma industry. Heres why. Herd immunity is the theory that if most people are vaccinated against a given illness, then the people of the community will be protected against that illness. The theory says that without herd immunity, there would be widespread outbreaks and deaths to multiple vaccine-preventable illnesses. According to “experts” including the CDC, the threshold to achieve herd immunity is 80-95% of people vaccinated against a given illness. We have never been close to achieving herd immunity for two reasons: The overwhelming majority of adults are not up to date in their immunisations. The efficacy of vaccines wanes over time, meaning protection from a vaccine “wears off”. Whooping cough for example (4-6 years). We are in contact with adults every day, with no immunity to these deadly diseases. There are millions of adults walking around with no vaccine-provided protection from many of the diseases that we are supposed to have met the herd immunity threshold for. We are nowhere close to vaccine - induced herd immunity and never have been. While herd immunity may not exist, herd mentality most definitely does. Health authorities, media commentators, and schools and their parent-teacher associations waste no opportunity in perpetuating this myth. Proponents have done such a thorough job of convincing the public that a parent who questions it is treated like someone who thinks the earth is flat or believes climate change is a conspiracy. On the contrary: an unprejudiced view of the science about vaccines, and an examination of history, clearly show that the herd immunity theory is - and always has been flawed. Shared via Alec Zeck. To the father who said that my boys were a walking disease and that he would never allow my boys to be around his child as they put his child's life in danger, I really do hope we bump into each other at the park one day. My boys are still learning about boundaries, and personal space. They absolutely love to cuddle, and would probably squish your child super dooper affectionately. They spread nothing but LOVE ♡ It would benefit others to know if your child was recently vaccinated though, because shedding is a very real thing! Not that I am particularly worried about it - I don't live in fear, but for those who are high risk - newborns, the elderly and the immunocompromised. It is written in the vaccine inserts, they are supposed to be given to read prior to any vaccination. - 'Vaccine recipients should attempt to avoid, wherever possible, close association with high risk individuals for up to 6 weeks post vaccination. - ‘Excretion of small amounts of live attenuated rubella from the nose or throat has occurred in the majority 7-28 days after vaccination’. - ‘Post licensing experience suggest that transmission of varicella virus in vaccine virus resulting in varicella infection may occur’. - Vaccine strain measles virus detected in urine of vaccinated child 37 days after vaccination. MMR is a live virus vaccine. Recently vaccinated individuals shed the virus and can infect others; especially the immune compromised. Recently vaccinated individuals are far more of a threat to vulnerable children than those who have not been vaccinated. https://jcm.asm.org/content/jcm/33/9/2485.full.pdf?fbclid=IwAR1Ko6OfW78GjsE3G2XjdHRG7dL9yFwtjh7aB94BJG-h3Px5vjW2zlaZYPU This particular vaccine insert also states that the duration of protection from the measles, mumps, rubella and varicella infection after vaccination is unknown, and that measles and varicella has been reported as adverse reactions following vaccination. Also stating 'as for any vaccine, vaccination may not result in protection in all vaccine recipients'. Medical Herd Immunity: - Parts of bacteria, genetically manipulated viruses - Excessive antibody, incorrect shapes - IgG 2 and 4 -> decreases cellular immunity - TH2 dominant, antibody only, no CMI - Individual protection wanes in 2-10years. Natural Herd Immunity: - Full bacteria; virus and bacteria - Less antibody, protective form IgG 1 and 3 - Enhances Cell mediated immunity - TH1 dominant, activated T-cells. - Individual protection can last a lifetime.

column31: We asked you guys who is more dangerous: Zuckerberg or Gates. Most of you said Gates, because he's powerful and influential and shaping health policy, while Zuckerberg is handling speech. But oh...it goes so much deeper. Zuckerberg is more dangerous, and here's why. First, Zuckerberg is 30 years younger, and has much more time left to control things. (Gates is 65.) He's also more technologically savvy, having participated in the creation of the way that most people communicate now -- social media. Control of speech is no small thing. The people who control the information that is shared shape the perception of the world around us. They can change what we believe, and how we behave. They can make us believe that things that aren't real, are; and that things that are real, aren't. (Case in point: they want us to believe v@x injury is extremely rare or impossible, even though that's not remotely true.) Second, Zuckerberg's influence is NOT limited to his control over speech. Not remotely. He has his hands in many different industries, similar to Gates...including pharmaceuticals. Zuckerberg's wife, Priscilla Chan, is a doctor. In 2016, they started CZ BioHub. This is a foundation dedicated to advancing pharma, essentially. It helps to develop vaccines and drugs and even find new technology to do so (including using machine learning to develop new methods of vaccine development). He has poured at least $600 million into this so far. Oh, and CZ BioHub also partners with the Gates Foundation and a number of universities. (It wasn't long after the formation of CZ BioHub that suddenly everyone was talking about 'fake news' and the censorship of natural health started ramping up. Coincidence??) Zuckerberg also has a number of other non-profits that he heads, including the Chan-Zuckerberg Initiative. This foundation gives grants to other organizations, and tries to shape educational policy as well as science. They don't hide this, but people also don't talk about it much. They are trying to shape the world just as much as Gates is...but they *also* control speech and perception via this platform. If Zuckerberg has managed to hide in plain sight and keep everyone thinking that he's just an aww-shucks billionaire who's trying to promote speech and connection and make the world a better place.... What do you think he will be able to do in 5 or 10 years? He's worth $107 billion right now (nearly as much as Gates' $120 billion). Look into his foundations. Look into what and who he is supporting. He is promoting the status quo and suppressing non-allopathic health because **he personally profits from doing so.** And we've only just scratched the surface on this. Concerned yet?

column31: For years, we went back and forth on vitamins for kids. We wanted to be sure that picky kids (often too busy to stop and eat much) didn't miss out on key nutrients. But we also didn't want to pay for something with junky ingredients that wasn't really benefiting them. The solution? Herbal multivitamins! Regular multivitamins use isolated nutrients in very high doses. Most are in forms that are difficult to absorb. Balanced Vitamin and Mineral Levels -- Read the label on any multivitamin, and you'll find the the amounts of vitamins and minerals vary widely from brand to brand. That's because we don't know exactly how much each person needs on a daily basis (varies by age, diet, activity level, etc.). Rather than try to guess, we rely on nature to choose! No Mega-Doses -- Our bodies can only absorb so much at once. The high doses in most supplements are just excreted by the body, which is not beneficial. An herbal multivitamin is in smaller doses that the body can actually use. Actual Food -- Lots of companies brag that their vitamins are "food-based." But how close to food are they, really? Ours are made from whole organic herbs, steeped in organic glycerin (and nothing else). Highly Bioavailable -- Since the vitamins and minerals are in the exact same forms as they're found in nature, they're easily absorbed and used by the body. Safe for MTHFR Mutations -- Whole herbs naturally contain methylfolate, which is safe for those with MTHFR mutations. (No folic acid!) Tastes Good -- Sweet, herbaceous and sometimes minty, it's delicious! Easy-to-Use Liquid -- No pills to swallow or chalky tablets to chew. Liquid can be taken alone or added to your favorite drink. It's the next best thing to eating a perfect diet from nature -- because it *is* from nature, in a concentrated, easy-to-use liquid formula. Have you ever tried an herbal multivitamin?

column31: The UK childhood vaccine schedule doesn't include Hep B at birth, so why are Australian parents being pressured into vaccinating their newborn babies with Hep B? Hep B vaccination in healthy children that don’t share homes with injected drug users or chronic Hep B carriers just doesn’t seem to be scientifically justified. 'Unless our children our rubbing their cerebrospinal fluids on other kids pericardial sacs, it might just be an unjustifiable fear'. On September 4, 2020, the Informed Consent Action Networks legal team filed a petition to request the withdrawal or suspension of the approval granted by the FDA for two Hepatitis B vaccines (Engerix-B and Recombivax HB) for infants and toddlers. "until a properly controlled and adequately powered double-blind trial of sufficient duration is conducted to assess the safety of these products as required pursuant to applicable federal statutes and regulations for licensing these products." ICANs petition states the following rationale for their request: "The clinical trials relied upon to license these products only assessed safety for up to five days after injection. Therefore, these trials did not comply with the applicable federal statutory and regulatory requirements necessary to prove they were safe prior to licensure. https://www.icandecide.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Petition-Hep-B-FINAL.pdf Seizure, febrile seizure, encephalitis, vasovagal syncope are all listed as adverse reactions that have occurred post vaccination. Did your pediatrician tell you that your child could be infected with Hepatitis B from other kids at the playground, daycare or school? Look at the nuance in the CDC’s description of viral transmission; detectable virus in body fluid vs. infectious body fluid is very different. 

So unless your daycare, school or park day includes kids rubbing their cerebrospinal fluids on other kid’s pericardial sacs, it might just be an unjustifiable fear. 

Hep B vaccination in healthy children that don’t share homes with injected drug users or chronic Hep B carriers just doesn’t seem to be scientifically justified. 

Print this CDC recommendation out for your pediatrician and highlight your concerns! Don’t forget to check out the Vaccine Safety section where it discusses our lack of knowledge as to whether Hep B vaccination has a causal role in neurologic, chronic, and autoimmune diseases.

column31: Vaccine Injury of a Medical Professional: Shared from Lori Sanchez. “Vaccine injuries do not only happen to infants and children, I was 39 when I became vaccine injured. I had been in the healthcare field since 2000. I was a surgical tech, medical assistant, my last job in a physician/hospital setting was as a surgery coordinator while going back to school for my RN. In college, NEVER not in any of my biology, microbiology, chemistry, pharmacology, anatomy and physiology, advanced anatomy and physiology, or any of my nursing classes did we ever discuss vaccine ingredients or adverse reactions. We were taught, what vaccine to give and at what age. What I have learned since becoming vaccine injured blows my mind!!! It infuriates me that this information is not taught to anyone entering the medical field?? Fun fact when I worked in primary care any vials of meds, were inventoried, took out of the box, put in a locked cabinet or refrigerator. The box and insert with all the crucial information was thrown in the garbage!!! Truth be told, I have always been leery of the one size fits all for vaccines. My first baby was over 9 pounds, my friends baby was born at 6 pounds 2 days before my son was born but they received the exact same dose of a vaccine because of their age? Every medicine given goes by age and weight except vaccines. I vaccinated my kids but I did delayed schedule and one or two vaccines at a time because it just didn’t seem right to me. And my kids skipped certain vaccines on the CDC schedule. Thankfully my kids are fine!! Anyway, I switched jobs to a new hospital (December 2013), prior to my employment starting I needed a pre-employment physical, they wanted me to repeat the Hep B series (which I had in college in 1998/1999) when my titers came back as 0. I have always refused the flu vaccine which was fine as long as I wore a mask during flu season. After the first shot, I was ridiculously tired, but I just contributed it from going from afternoons to a 6 am shift. A month later I had the second shot and that’s when all hell broke loose in my body.” Full story: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/vaccine-injury-of-a-medical-professional/

column31: Friends, we are the gatekeepers of our homes. If we are not intentional about reading labels, we may be using toxic items as many will contain an ingredient vaguely called “fragrance.” This catch-all term acts a little bit of a loophole in most cases — because fragrances can be easily replicated with a list of ingredients, they’re considered trade secrets, allowing companies to keep their recipes under lock and key. When it states "fragrance", the kicker is - we don’t know what’s really in these products. According to the Environmental Working Group, the fragrance industry operates with about 3100 stock chemical ingredients, and the average “fragrance” in personal care and household products contains at least 15 of these chemicals that are NOT listed on the label. Also, there are hundreds that can fall into the category of fragrance. And 80% of these chemicals have NEVER been tested for safety. You might be wondering, how is this even allowed to happen? Like I mentioned fragrance acts as a loophole on the FDA's regulation of personal care products. They're considered "trade secret" under the Fair Package and Labeling Act of 1966, which allows companies to NOT list their ingredients so that their formula cannot be replicated easily. Unfortunately, this gives brands the opportunity to add in cost-effective, but toxic, chemicals to their product to make it smell better and last longer. Most common components of “fragrance” contain phthalates — these are known to cause cancer and disrupt hormones. We’re actually looking at significant damage to male’s sperm, affecting fertility, and concentration of musk ketone in breast tissue for women. So what do these fragrances do to the human body? We don't entirely know to the full extent, however, we know that short term exposure to fragrance has been known to ⚠️ trigger migraines, respiratory issues, dizziness, nausea, central nervous system dysfunction, speech, throat/eye/mouth/skin irritation, kidney damage, ataxia and more. These are just a few know chemicals under the label "fragrance": acetone; benzaldehyde; benzyl acetate; benzyl alcohol; camphor; ethanol; ethyl acetate; limonene; linalool; methylene chloride, and methyl benzene (toluene). Toluene is considered hazardous waste. It's flammable and volatile, and it attacks the central nervous system, blood, liver, kidneys, eyes and skin and acts as an asthma trigger. Methylene chloride is what's found in septic tank cleaners and pesticides. "According to the Committee on Science & Technology, “Approximately 95% of chemicals used in fragrances are synthetic compounds derived from petroleum.” “Petroleum based chemicals are being found to cause significant attritional effects to the nervous system and immune system after prolonged exposure. ⚠️ Illnesses identified in the medical research include adult and child cancers, numerous neurological disorders, immune system weakening, autoimmune disorders, asthma, allergies, infertility, miscarriage, and child behavior disorders including learning disabilities, mental retardation, hyperactivity and ADD (attention deficit disorders) and cancers.” 👆If you are experiencing any of the above, it is time to re-evaluate, because nothing is more important than your health and wellness - and feeling vibrant, I can personally attest to that! Of any time in history - now is the time to ditch and switch chemicals, your health & quality of life depends on it. I'm happy to walk you through how I switched out chemicals in my life, without overwhelm and with bite sized baby steps. ✨

column31: The new edition of Raising a Vaccine Free Child is now available in digital format from Kindle, as well as in paperback from vaccinefreechild.com. This book provides parents with a comprehensive guide to the facts, myths, problems, and solutions associated with raising a vaccine free child. It explains the difference between the self-resolving childhood diseases and the group of infectious diseases that need holistic intervention. Measles and chicken pox are examples of self-resolving diseases that require careful management, while polio and tetanus are examples of diseases that need holistic intervention to make them go away. Parents are provided with scientifically-based advice on how to bring children safely through the childhood diseases. Doctors and nurses are trained to treat the childhood diseases in ways that increase the risk of complications, and they are not taught that many scientific studies show that the childhood diseases reduce the risk of chronic diseases like cancer and heart disease in later life. Raising a Vaccine Free Child provides information about the toxic ingredients and biological contaminants in vaccines, and the relationship between vaccination and the global epidemic of chronic disease. A detailed chapter on “herd immunity” empowers parents to withstand the accusation that vaccine free children pose a threat to others. The book provides an insight into the workings of the vaccine industry, and it shows that the long-term adverse effects of vaccination have not been properly assessed at any time in any country. Readers will learn that vaccination is not the reason for the absence of some infectious diseases, and that insidious, long-term adverse effects of vaccination are common. column31: When I look at Holly’s face and her beaming smile I see my daughter. I don’t remember the exact moment I came across Holly Stavola’s story. I don’t remember if it was her mother describing the story in a vaxxed stories, or if it was her family’s website that I stumbled into, but her story alone was enough to make me never want to vaccinate. It was enough to me as a reason why we should never, and I mean NEVER, mandate vaccines. It’s why we should never force a parent to choose between their child’s education and their child’s health. It’s why we should not intervene in the doctor – patient relationship, and a perfect example of when a State Law has gone too far. When or if a medical procedure could end untowardly, in death, it should never be required or mandated of any group of people. PERIOD. “On February 4th, 2000, Holly Stavola, a daughter, a sibling, a grandchild, and a niece died tragically and unnecessarily from encephalopathy due to her 2nd MMR vaccination, which was required of her for Kindergarten. Holly was a completely healthy, bright, kind and beautiful 5 year old child. The day she received her vaccinations at her 5 year well check-up. Holly was not sick nor immunocompromised in any way. She received the MMR, the oral polio (which was no longer recommended as of Jan. 2000), the DTaP, the Mantoux test, and my son received the Chickenpox Vaccine (he was 9 years old). She became very ill a week following the shots, which is within the expected time period, a vaccine table injury of encephalopathy. Encephalopathy is one of the potential reactions of the MMR as stated in the Merck Package Insert and the vaccinetable.html on the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services. It can occur between 5-15 days after the vaccine. She suffered 65 hours before becoming brain dead. Her first symptoms were a 107 degree fever and seizure that happened in our house before calling 911. In the first hospital we were screaming for help; they did a spinal tap to check for meningitis, and with increasing brain inflammation this should not have been done. column31: Here are some of the best things you can do to stay well. Wash your hands -- This is the single most important thing. Wash your hands every few hours, after using the bathroom, before eating, and any time you have been away from home. Use regular soap and water (not antibacterial, which can negatively impact gut flora). If you can't wash, especially after touching door handles, payment kiosks, and other high-touch spaces in public, use a hand sanitizer where the active ingredient is 60% ethanol or higher. Don't touch your face! -- It's a habit for many, but if you touch a contaminated surface then touch your face, you're more likely to get sick. Avoid touching for any reason if you are in public, until you can wash your hands. (Even if you wear gloves...don't touch!) Stay home if you're sick! -- Symptomatic people are the primary ones who spread illness. If you have a fever, vomiting, or diarrhea, just stay in. If you are coughing heavily, stay in. Avoid crowds. If you MUST go out, consider wearing a mask and wash your hands immediately before you leave your home. Symptoms need to be gone for at least 24 hours **without** any type of medication before it's safe to venture out. Eat healthy -- Shore up your immune system by making sure you are getting plenty of fresh foods and all the necessary nutrients. Some nutrient deficiencies can increase your risk of getting sick (like vitamin C, D, and zinc and selenium). Avoid sugar and pro-inflammatory foods, as they can lower your immune system. Exercise moderately -- A brisk walk, some jumping jacks, whatever you enjoy. 10 to 20 minutes per day is good for most, and don't overdo it especially if you're not used to regular exercise. Too much exercise can have the opposite effect. Stay well, friends!
column34: Best Practices to WASH HANDS OFTEN Stay Well Use soap and water, wash for 20 sec. Or 60% alcohol-based sanitizer. DON'T TOUCH YOUR FACE Avoid mouth, nose, eyes until hands are washed. STAY HOME IF YOU'RE SICK 24 hours after fever, vomiting, diarrhea, or heavy coughing resolve *without* medication. EAT HEALTHY Fresh fruits, veggies, unprocessed foods. Avoid sugar, white flour, polyunsaturated vegetable oils. EXERCISE LIGHTLY Brisk walking or other light-to-moderate exercise daily, 10 20 min. Avoid overly strenuous exercise. column31: During pregnancy and birth, many women do not get informed choices. Since about 50% of women in the US now get Pitocin (synthetic oxytocin) at some point during labor, it's important to know the risks! The greatest risks with Pitocin are with women who are induced at or near term, when their bodies and babies aren't ready yet. In fact, Pitocin is *not* indicated for elective inductions. Risks can include a greater likelihood of c-section or use of epidurals (which come with their own risks). Fever is also a risk, which can lead to potentially unnecessary antibiotic use, destroying maternal and neonatal gut health and increasing potential resistance. Pitocin can also lead to hyperstimulation of the uterus, which can put the baby in distress, be extremely uncomfortable to the mother, or increase the risk of uterine rupture. High levels or long use of Pitocin can increase the risk of retained placenta, which can also increase the risk of both immediate and delayed postpartum hemorrhage. Once the baby is born, having had Pitocin affects the establishment of breastfeeding (and we know that when breastfeeding is established in the first few hours, moms are more likely to exclusively breastfeed for longer). There are minimal studies about the long-term effects on babies, but some suggest that motor development is negatively affected, even 5 years later. There is good news! When Pitocin use is minimal, is limited to cases where labor induction is truly needed, used after 39 weeks, or used to augment labor that is already established, the risks are lower. Preterm, elective, high-dose, or long-term use (long labor) increases the risks. Sources: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4982443/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26011378:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26011378/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18342288:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18342288/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23571133:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23571133/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23181343:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23181343/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6494504/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3555986/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/31032882:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31032882/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6789409/

column31: There has been a lot of confusion about supplements lately. Some people have gotten the idea that "if a little is good, more must be better" when it comes to certain nutrients. Or, they've confused the amounts that are beneficial when not feeling well with amounts that should be used daily. Here's where we stand: for the most part, in most situations, mega-doses are bad. Every vitamin and mineral has an 'agonist' and an 'antagonist' in the body -- usually several. When someone takes a regular mega-dose of one nutrient, it causes the body to have high levels of that nutrient, PLUS all of the agonists. It causes deficiencies in all of the antagonists. For example, calcium and magnesium compete for absorption in the body. Take way too much calcium and it will lead to a magnesium deficiency. What we really need is balance. That's the holistic view. No nutrient is more important than another (generally speaking); we need all of them, in the right amounts, to be healthy. We trust nature, and our own instincts, for this balance. Healthy foods and herbs have what we need, in the right amounts. Mega-dose pills don't. (Ever notice that your pee turns bright yellow after taking a supplement? That's all the vitamins you didn't absorb.) Stick with nature. Naturally healthy and in balance.

column31: It’s not like the cv is joining a well studied vaccine schedule. None of the other injections currently in use were tested against inert placebos, and retrospective studies routinely lack a completely unvaccinated control group. It’s not like every medical provider has ever even heard of VAERS, let alone report reactions. We are walking into a field full of land mines, not roses. How can we claim vaccines are safe if we aren’t even collecting the data that *could* possibly prove that hypothesis wrong? In 2011, HHS funded a research team "to improve the quality of vaccination programs by improving the quality of physician adverse vaccine event detection and reporting to the national Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System (VAERS).” However, what they found was: "Adverse events from drugs and vaccines are common, but underreported. Although 25% of ambulatory patients experience an adverse drug event, less than 0.3% of all adverse drug events and 1-13% of serious events are reported to the Food and Drug Administration (FDA). Likewise, fewer than 1% of vaccine adverse events are reported. Low reporting rates preclude or slow the identification of “problem” drugs and vaccines that endanger public health." And then, A 2013 survey titled “Who is unlikely to report adverse events after vaccinations to the Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System (VAERS)? found that while 37% of healthcare providers had identified at least one adverse event following immunization, “only 17% of them had ever reported to VAERS.” Astonishingly, 29% of healthcare providers had NEVER even heard of VAERS. Read more: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/how-to-report-a-vaccine-reaction/ #vaers #vaersisproof #vaccinate #vaxfacts #vaccinesafetyadvocate #vaccines #covidvaccine #flushot #publichealth #medicalfreedom #informedconsent #endmandates

column31: A lot of times, advice that is passed around the internet doesn't come with qualifiers, subtleties, and gray areas. One such topic is mint while breastfeeding. Many women have heard "Don't use mint while breastfeeding!" Not everyone knows why, or what herbs are even considered mint! The truth is, mint won't hurt your baby, but it could affect your supply. Some women are very sensitive to any type of mint, and even a mild mint tea could lower their production. Other women are not sensitive to mint, and are fine to use it. Peppermint essential oil is going to be the strongest "mint" and is best avoided unless you *know* that you're not sensitive to it, until your supply is well-established. Other forms of mint -- which, yes, includes lavender! -- are safe in herb form for the majority of women. Next time you hear "No mint while breastfeeding!" share this graphic and help people be informed!
column34: The short answer: Probably. Many women use mint with no effects on supply. If supply is well-established. or a mom has over-supply, they are fine to try mint. HERBS IN THE MINT FAMILY: *Peppermint *Nettles *Spearmint *Sage *Lavender *Lemon balm *Catnip *Hyssop WHO SHOULD AVOID MINT? 1) Women with a personal or family history of mint causing reduction in supply 2) Women whose supply is not yet established (prior to 6 weeks) 3) Women who are struggling with supply Earthley -weliness-

column31: Friends, I believe it's safe to say we can all use some EXTRA emotional support right about now! I know I can 🙋‍♀️ So, in lieu of the events of the world and country, let's talk the dreamy effects of the new Vanilla Oleoresin ~and~ how therapeutic oils help rewire our thoughts, traumas and beliefs. This essential oil is so sweet, and buttery right out of the bottle. Here are some roller blends (or diffuser blends) to give you that dreamy aroma of vanilla, that you can also use in your diffuser or in a roller ball as a perfume. 💦 Hit the share button to save for later!! Roller Blends with Vanilla Oleoresin. For each recipe below, combine essential oils in a 10 mL roller bottle. Top off with a neutral carrier oil, such as Young Living V-6, sweet almond oil or extra virgin olive oil. Or simply diffuse! +Spiced Creamsicle Vanilla and orange combine for that sweet, creamsicle aroma, while cinnamon or clove add just a hint of spice to this blend. ◐ ◐ ◐ drops vanilla oleoresin ◐ ◐ ◐ drops orange essential oil ◐ ◐ ◐ drops cinnamon bark or clove essential oil +Focused & Grounded The bottom note of sandalwood and Frank provides grounding and balances the root chakra. ◐ ◐ ◐ drops frankincense essential oil ◐ ◐ ◐ drops sandalwood essential oil ◐ ◐ ◐ drops vanilla oleoresin +Autumn Sleep Roll this blend on at bedtime to fall asleep faster with sweet dreams. ◐ ◐ ◐ drops vanilla oleoresin ◐ ◐ ◐ drops patchouli essential oil ◐ ◐ ◐ drops cedarwood essential oil Let's talk about how essential oils impact our thoughts, traumas, beliefs and stuck emotions! To do this, we need to understand a little bit about how our brains work. Within your brain is something called the limbic system. This is referred to as the emotional center of your brain, because literally every thought, emotion, conscious and unconscious memory, knee-jerk reaction, personality trait, feeling of stress, or life lesson you’ve ever experienced, is thought to be held here, in your limbic system. It’s like a storage unit, and one of its jobs is to help you to process current situations in the tiniest fraction of a second to help you to determine, based on past situations, what is the best or safest way for you to think, feel, or react now? This is a self-preservation mechanism, basically to ensure that you are playing it safe, hanging out in your comfort zone and that no harm is going to come to you. All this information is stored in a way that keeps it pretty inaccessible to you as well, which is why it’s so frustrating when we’re trying to change these things, and we feel like we can’t do it. Think of your thoughts and emotions like wagon wheels, just traveling the same pathways over and over until they create these really deep ruts. ☸️ We literally get stuck in these thought or emotional patterns, these ruts in our mind, and it can feel really impossible to get out of. Now, also within your limbic system is something called your olfactory bulb. This is literally your sense of smell. The olfactory bulb transmits smell information from the nose to the brain, and is thus necessary for a proper sense of smell. As a neural circuit, the olfactory bulb has one source of sensory input, and one output. And this is really unique because it’s the only one of your senses that’s processed in this part of your brain, right alongside your thoughts and emotions. Your olfactory bulb relays information directly into your limbic system. But it’s not just relaying smells. It’s actually relaying the things associated with smell. This is because your olfactory neurons themselves are capable of learning and remembering information, and they’re constantly undergoing something called neurogenesis, meaning they’re constantly renewing. Every six to 10 weeks, they are brand new neurons, ready to take in new information, and relay that to your limbic system as new messages. By the way, researchers are actually finding these olfactory neurons all over our body. Did you know your liver can actually smell what’s going through it? Let’s shift gears and talk about the oils for a minute. Essential oils are made up of natural and aromatic compounds. Most people understand how they work physically on the body. Lavender & Frankincense soothes and calms irritated skin, thyme oil supports balanced progesterone and peppermint supports digestion, and teal tree oil support deep healing of wounds. Just as these oils work with different systems of the body, the aromatic compounds are also working within the systems of your brain. Working through that olfactory bulb, some oils are going to calm certain areas of the limbic system. Others are going to stimulate. It can bring up memories, they can help us process trauma, they can increase confidence and courage, all by interacting with the limbic system, either by themselves or, this is where it gets juicy when you’re using them with other (truncated)

column6: I believe in informed consent. Always. Vaccines wasn't something I really thought about until I became a mama. Here to share what I have researched along the way. I am a RN.
column31: Prime Minister Scott Morison, has proudly announced that Australia has just entered into two further vaccines agreements with Novavax and Pfizer/BioNTech with a cost to taxpayers of $1.5 billion dollars. The Prime Minister announced an investment of $1.7 billion dollars to secure vaccines from Oxford/AstraZeneca and University of Queensland /CSL, bringing the total dollars spent on vaccine pipeline procurement to $3.2 billion. The newly acquired Pfizer/BioNTech vaccine, contains genetic material messenger called mRNA. Scientists and ethicists are abounding alarms about this new, untested, and very controversial experimental RNA technology. MRNA vaccines are a form of genetic engineering called “germ line editing”, with these genetic alterations passed down to future generations. In January the Geneva Statement, the world’s leading ethicists and scientists, called for an end to this kind of experimentation. “The ‘Geneva Statement on Heritable Human Genome Editing: The Need for Course Correction’ points to the need to clarify misrepresentations, center societal consequences and concerns, and foster meaningful public empowerment and deliberation on the potential uses of this species-altering technology. It is a robust and cautionary statement about the future of heritable genome editing that seeks to disrupt the current trajectory of discussions about the applications of this technology and demands broad societal consensus before any decision is made about whether to allow its use in humans". Keep in mind that Covid vaccines have been allowed to skip the critical animal testing phase in order to get products out to market as quickly as possible. Renowned Doctor Peter Hotez warns of potentially fatal consequences of skipping animal studies “if there is immune enhancement in animals, that’s a showstopper”. Former NIH Scientist Judy Mikovits says it’s criminal to test MRNA vaccines on humans, “MRNA can cause cancers and other dire harms that don’t surface for years”. The associated risks with the multitude of unknowns, minimal testing and rushing to market are evident, and disturbing to say the least. The Oxford/AstraZeneca vaccine has been plagued with issues throughout the trials, which were paused globally when a participant from the UK trials contracted transverse myelitis. The trials have since resumed globally in all countries except for the United States. This same vaccine trial has tragically cost a 28 year old doctor in Brazil, a phase three trial participant, his life. Interestingly, this doctor was part of the placebo testing group. He was not administered an inert placebo as one would assume; he was reportedly being dosed with a market approved meningococcal vaccine. The Prime Minister advised that Novavax will supply 40 million vaccine doses and Pfizer/BioNTech will provide 10 million, if the vaccines are proven safe and effective. With these vaccines being rushed to market, is there any way to know if the vaccines are either safe or effective by the time the first doses are administered in early 2021? Here are some comments on the situation from pro maskers: "I'm tired of having to confront people," wrote Michael Daigh of St. Paul, who recalled a confrontation while waiting to check-out at a suburban-metro big box. "Of course there just had to be that one dude. I don't seek them out, or appoint myself the mask police, but if they're in a radius of me, like at checkout today, then I say something." "I said 'hey, special little guy (he was not that little) I'm going to need you to back up.'... Everyone around did the Minnesota thing of staring at their shoes. The poor cashiers did nothing, but did apologize to me when it was my turn." "I won’t support a business who does not have the health of their customers and their families as a priority at this time," writes a reader named Becky from Alexandria. "Furthermore, if they are choosing to be so bold as to push the no-mask agenda, then I will not choose to do business with them when the pandemic is over either." "I had to dodge singles and groups of unmasked people roaming the aisles. The store is not that big and aisles are narrow in places, so avoiding people was difficult. Staff members did nothing that I could see to gain compliance." "I have informed my supervisor that I'm not feeling at all safe in my environment," she writes. "Nothing's changed. I was told we don't have mask police, so I should just do the basics. ... I used to love my job. Now I have to take an anxiety pill to go in the door." If you are that scared, STAY HOME. Do not try to punish, guilt trip, or harass those that choose NOT to wear a mask. column31: Many people are wearing masks either out of choice or force. So we wanted to share some safety guidelines for wearing masks. 1. Wash Masks Often -- If your mask *is* washable (not all are). Wash on hot and dry hot as well, to kill germs. 2. Make Sure Mask Fits Properly -- It should cover both your nose and mouth and should fit tightly to your face. It shouldn't be open at the sides or bottom. 3. Wash Your Hands After Removing Mask -- Your mask may have become contaminated while out, so once it is removed (carefully!), place it in a safe location or storage container, and wash your hands before touching your face. 4. Avoid Masks While Driving -- There is no need to wear a mask while alone in your car, and at least one person has crashed from lack of oxygen. Put your mask on once you have parked and are ready to exit, but don't wear while driving. 5. Avoid Masks While Exercising -- You have an increased need for oxygen while exercising, and a mask can make it difficult to get the air you need. Skip the mask and exercise in an open area, away from other people (or exercise at home). 6. Remove Mask if you Feel Light-Headed -- Your safety matters, and if you're not breathing well or feel like you're going to pass out, remove your mask and breathe. Someone having to resuscitate you and touch your mask is worse than you removing it yourself so that you don't faint. Be smart. Be safe. If you choose to wear a mask, do it properly and only when you must.

Their secret? No matter who wins the U.S. election, we can choose to: ☀️ be present ☀️ enjoy nature ☀️ nurture relationships ☀️ laugh ☀️ love These are simple pleasures full of love, light, truth. 🙌🏼 No one, anywhere, can take these from us—regardless of position or influence. 🧡 This is why I do not live or die by who takes office come January. column31: For many decades, there were only a few vaccines recommended for infants and children prior to school. One of them, the DPT vaccine, had some very severe side effects, including brain swelling, seizure, and death which was brought to light through the 1982 NBC broadcast DPT: Vaccine Roulette by reporter Lea Thompson. This increased awareness in turn increased lawsuits: “Between 1978 and 1981 only nine product liability suits were filed against DTP manufacturers but by the mid-1980s lawsuits rose to over 200 per year. The lawsuits destabilized the DTP vaccine market, causing two of the three manufacturers to withdraw, leaving only Lederle Laboratories, which estimated its tort liability exceeded its annual sales by a factor of 200.” In response to pressure from drug companies, Congress passed the National Childhood Vaccine Injury Act in 1986 (H.R. 5546), which gave complete liability protection to pharmaceutical companies for injuries and deaths that resulted from vaccines. The US government set up the ‘Vaccine Injury Compensation Program’ to handle injury petitions. The no-fault legal alternative is funded by a .75 cent excise tax added to each vaccine dose, paid for by consumers and tax payers. From 1988 to 2020, total payouts for injuries from vaccine currently exceed $4.4 billion. However, there is a very limited table of injuries, the petition has to be filed no later than 3 years from the injury, or 2 years from a death, and the petitioner has to provide burden of proof, which can be difficult while caring for an injured child or grieving a dead child, or being injured yourself. Removing all liability enabled a consequence-free market for the drug companies, and our schedule quadrupled as a result. It was never about health. #publichealth #vicp #vaers #doctors #nurse #pediatrics #wellbaby #2monthshots #thirdtrimester #duedate #baby #wellcheck #shots #shotsshotsshots #babyshots #babyshower #family #wellness #health #mamaknowsbest Advocacy Shop: https://circleofmamas.com/store/
